description1.name: Description
description1.value: "WELL CARED FOR 2 STOREY, 3 BEDROOM & 1-4PC BATH HOME, ENCLOSED FRONT PORCH ON LARGE 50 FT X 201.10 FT LOT ON VERY QUIET & SAFE STREET IN JORDAN STATION WITH UPDATED KITCHEN AND APPROX 1350 SQ FT OF LIVING SPACE WITH FULL HEIGHT BASEMENT" Welcome to 4138 Queen Victoria St in Jordan. Situated in the Town of Jordan Station between St. Catharines & Beamsville is truly a great place to live & raise a family in a safe area if you want the opportunity of Country Living (on municipal services) and within 5-10 mins of the City. You notice this home is on a quiet treed street and large lot. Enter into the spacious front enclosed front porch (great for relaxing on those beautiful summer evenings. Enter inside, you are greeted with a spacious foyer area with lots of wood trim and stunning French Doors leading into a bright, Large Open Living Rm & Dining Rm combination with Wood Stove, hardwood flooring and lots of windows to allow the natural sunlight. Off the Dining Rm, you have a beautiful updated kitchen (2020) with lots of counter and cabinet space with double sink. Next, head upstairs to 3 generous sized bedrooms with plenty of closet space and a 4pc bath. The basement offers full height with an office and landry area and can easily be finished. Once you have completed the inside, enjoy your large treed back yard with plenty of room for a pool & trampoline and pets and a large deck area off the kitchen for bbq and entertaining. Only a bike ride to the town of Jordan, Balls Falls, Bruce Trail, wineries, and Jordan Harbour & Lake Ontario and 5 minutes from both St. Catharines & Beamsville. Experience what Country Living is all about. You will not be disappointed. (Kitchen - 2020, Roof-2017, Furnace 2014)

summary.name: Summary
value: The home is a 2-storey, 3-bedroom, and 1-4 piece bathroom home.
It is located on a 50 ft x 201.10 ft lot in a quiet and safe street in Jordan Station.
The home has approximately 1350 sq ft of living space with a full height basement.
The kitchen was updated in 2020 and features double sinks and plenty of counter and cabinet space.
The home has a spacious front enclosed porch, a large open living room and dining room combination, and hardwood flooring.
The home has three generous-sized bedrooms with plenty of closet space and a 4-piece bathroom.
The home is located near the town of Jordan, Balls Falls, Bruce Trail, wineries, and Jordan Harbour & Lake Ontario.
